text: testified as follows:
- - - EXAMINATION

Good morning, Rosemary.  My name is Joseph Blum, and I represent Mercedes-Benz in a series of claims that have been brought about the fire that occurred here in 2016. I'm just going to ask you a series of questions this morning. Any time you don't understand my question, please tell me immediately and I'll be happy to restate the question for you.  If you don't hear the question, please let me know and I'll be happy to restate it or read it back for you. I'm going to ask you to please try to keep all your responses verbal today, because the court reporter cannot take down nods of the head or shrugging of your shoulders.  Do you understand all that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes, sir.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Is there anything that would prevent you from hearing my questions today and understanding them and answering accurately?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Are you employed by Clemens?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Tell us in what capacity you're employed?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: You want the job title, job duties?
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Why don't we start with the job title?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I'd just say manager.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And how long have you been in that position?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: You would have to ask Randy.  I don't know.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Let's go back even more basically then.  How long have you worked here at Clemens?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I think I started part time like in 2006.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And prior to 2006 were you employed in any way?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Where were you employed?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I was selling real estate.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: You're a licensed real estate agent?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes, sir, yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And how long did you do that for?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: All right.  And before becoming a real estate agent, were you also employed?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And in what capacity?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: The last job before the Realtor job?
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Sure.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I don't recall.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Tell us generally what your educational background is?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Some college.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  Where did you get that college at?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Montgomery County.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And when you were at Montgomery County, did you specialize in your studies --
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Business.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: After leaving Montgomery County and before becoming a real estate agent, can you just tell us generally the types of work that you did?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I was working part time.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: In restaurant, hospitality.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And are you related to the Clemens family that operates this business?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I'm married to Randy.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And when did you and Randy get married?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: All right.  And you described your title as a manager.  Tell us just generally what you do on a day-to-day basis?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I do bookkeeping, invoicing, sales.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And were you employed here in 2014?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And were you working generally as a manager in 2014?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I was doing sales, managing that department, yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And in 2014 you were back in the old facility before the fire; correct?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Correct.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  Did you have an office in that building?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Where was that office located?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: In the front with all the other ones.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: I'm going to mark a document, if we could, as Exhibit 19, to your deposition.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: (Floor plan diagram marked Rosemary Exhibit 1.)
I'm going to show you a document which we marked as Exhibit 1 to your deposition.  I'm going to ask you to take a moment and look at that. Have you ever seen this document before?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  This is a document that was produced during the litigation which purports to show the floor plan of the building here, the old building at Clemens.  Do you recognize what would be the front part of the building? Is it the bottom of the diagram?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: If you say so.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And if that is accurate, that's the 5th Street side of the building is at the bottom, do you see there's a diagram that shows offices across the front wall?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: So are you going from 2 to 12, is that what you're talking -- am I looking at that right?
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Yes, that is correct, from 2 to 12.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: And the question was?  I'm sorry.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Do you see where I'm at in terms of those offices?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Right.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Do you recognize which of those offices you were working in back in 2014?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I really can't make this stuff out.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  I'm going -- you can put the diagram down -- I'm going to ask you a different question then. If, before the fire at the old building, if I was standing on 5th Street and I looked at the front of the building, there were offices there and windows across the front; correct?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Uh-huh.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Is that correct?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Right.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  You have to say yes or no because of her taking it down.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: When we stood there and looked at those offices back in 2014, could you tell me if I was standing on 5th Street where your office was located?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: So at the corner of 5th Street and Mitchell, there's a break room.  Right next to that was my office.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And if we went, like if we were standing there, the break room, your office, and then further down to the left there were other offices that went down along there; is that correct?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And if we were standing out on 5th Street and there was a break room and your office, the company had a time clock that people punched.  Where was that time clock located?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: By the break room.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  So it would have been at what I would call the extreme right-hand side of the --
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: On the wall.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And at some point in time there was a video surveillance system put into the building.  Are you familiar with that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Cameras, correct.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Do you know when it went in?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Do you know who put it in?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And in April of 2014, do you recall an incident wherein there was a truck fire here in the parking lot?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Tell me what you know about that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I came to work and the truck was on fire.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  So when you arrived here, the incident had already started?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.  The Sprinter was on fire.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And did you that morning talk to anybody about what occurred?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Who did you talk to?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Everybody that was here, workers.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And what were you told had occurred that morning?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: That the driver pulled the truck out, parked it in the parking lot, came back in, someone from another plant banged on the back door and said, "You have a truck on fire."
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And do you know who it was that pulled the truck out that morning?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Johnny.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Johnny, do you know his last name?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.  Should be on the record here somewhere.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And did you ever have any discussion with anyone about what occurred, how that fire started?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No one knows.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And have you had any discussions with anyone about that, though, in terms of anybody who investigated or what caused the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I talked to the fire police or the fire chief.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And what did he say?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: What did he ask me?
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: What did he say, did he say anything?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: He asked me questions.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And do you remember what questions he asked you?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: What I saw.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And when you arrived, did you pull into the parking lot and saw the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I park out front.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And when you parked out in front, how did you discover it?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Walked through the building.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And when you walked through the building, did someone alert you to the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I got called on the way to work.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Who called you?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: My husband, Randy.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And what did he say?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: "Are you at work yet?"
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And did he say there was any reason why he was asking you that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yeah.  I asked him why.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And what did he say?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: That there's a fire.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And when you arrived, did you immediately then go to the back of the building?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And what did you observe actually?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: That the truck was on fire.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Was it just one truck or were there multiple trucks on fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: It began with one truck, the front of the truck was on fire, then it spread to the other two vehicles that were next to it because it was too hot, nobody could move them.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: When you personally walked out there the first time, was just the Sprinter on fire or --
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Correct.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Had the fire department arrived at the scene?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: The fire police were here and they were pulling in.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  How long did it take them to put out the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I have no idea.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Switching now to the day before the fire occurred here at the plant, the actual building, were you here that day?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And how long were you here?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I work full time.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And when you work full time, does it mean you're on the premises most of the time?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: How often are you in the building or --
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: It all depends.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: So going back to June of 2016, do you remember what your job responsibilities were at that time?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: June of 2016 I was working from home.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And what were your job responsibilities at that time?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Pretty much the same except I didn't -- I wasn't doing first aid sales anymore.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: First aid what?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Sales.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And did you ever come into the office during that period when you were working at home?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I did come in, I was training someone.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And do you know, were you on the premises the day before the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I was at home.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Do you know how long it was from the last time before the fire you were on the premises?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: If we were standing on the 5th Street side of the building, again, looking at all the windows, could you describe for me just from the right-hand side of the building going to the left what the general operational layout was inside the plant?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: The plant offices or what?
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: The plant, the physical plant where the work got done?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: So there was washing machines, folding, dryers, steam thing, and then the trucks, yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: So was it divided up that the one side of the building, like if we were on 5th Street, the right side of the building would have been more what I would call the dirty side of the operation?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: You mean -- well, I don't know.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And you mentioned that you were in first aid sales.  Tell me what you did for that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: At the time I still do the billing and everything, at the time I would go to customers.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And what were you selling?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: First aid, first aid kits, first aid products.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And did you sell any of the laundry services that the company was performing?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: So the day that the fire occurred, how did you learn about the fire?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: Got a phone call.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And who did you get that phone call from?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I didn't get the phone call.  Randy got the phone call in the middle of the night.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And did you personally come here that night?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I did later, yeah.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And the day after the fire were you involved in any way in terms of trying to keep the business going or making sure the business moved forward?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I did not come in and do any of that.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And did your employment continue after the fire occurred?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I did different stuff, bought stuff that, you know, we had to move into the back building, so.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And when you say the back building, tell me which building you moved into?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: The building behind this building.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  And was that building empty when you moved in there?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: There was one unit empty that we moved into.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And were there tenants in the other units in the back building?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I don't know all that --
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: -- how many were there.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And how long did you then operate out of the back building?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: I don't know exactly how long it was.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: All right.  And were you involved in any of the purchasing of what I'll call replacement like inventory, uniforms, anything like that?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And were you involved in any way with the reconstruction of the building itself?
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: I have no further questions.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: - - - EXAMINATION
Ma'am, I just have one.  My name is Dan Divis, I represent Bergey's. The back building, who owns that building?
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: We do.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Do you know when the purchase was, approximately?
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: I don't.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Was that building purchased at the same time that the building here was purchased?
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: You would have to get the date, no. That was a recent purchase.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Recent meaning, can you estimate how long it is that you --
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: I don't know if it was 2015 or 2016.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Was it after the fire that --
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: It was before the fire.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Okay.  Do you know how long before the fire --
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: No, I don't know.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: Just wait till I get the whole question out because the court reporter can only take one person taking at a time.  Just let me make sure. Was the back building purchased before the fire here in this building?
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: Yes.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: And do you know how long it is before the fire that that building had been purchased by Clemens?
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: No.
speaker: THE WITNESS

text: That's all I have. Thank you.
speaker: MR. DIVIS

text: Nothing from me.
speaker: MR. ACKLEN

text: I have no questions.
speaker: MR. MILLIS

text: No questions.
speaker: MR. REICH

text: That's it.
speaker: MR. BLUM

text: (Witness excused.)
(Whereupon the deposition adjourned at 10:16 a.m.)
